an estimated 50,000 young people jammed the streets of this desert resort saturday for traditional spring break revelry, watched closely by a reinforced police presence
at least 15 arrests occurred during the day, mostly for trespassing in hotels or public drunkenness, on top of roughly four times as many arrests friday night
another 15 arrests, mostly for public drunkenness, were reported in the evening as the young visitors took to their cars and created gridlock
the traffic right now is backed up past the (aerial) tramway, which is several miles out of town,'' said sgt. ron starrs, adding that no major disturbances were reported
the 100-degree heat kept many partying high school and college students indoors earlier. those who chose to saunter under clear skies wore ``bathing suits, shorts, tanks tops, as little as possible,'' said police officer karen holtz, who estimated the number of visitors at 50,000 in a city with a population of 36,000
