soldiers raided the village of maythalun, about 8 miles north of nablus, at 2 a.m. sunday, said the arab-owned palestine press service. protests broke out and soldiers opened fire, killing three, it said
an army spokesman confirmed the clashes but not the deaths, the reports of which he said were being investigated
troops opened fire after arabs attacked them with axes and stones and tried to run them over with two cars as they were leaving the village after making arrests, the army spokesman said
a nurse at al ittihad hospital in nablus identified the dead as omar mahmoud rabaiyeh, 23, who died of a gunshot wound to the heart, sahim mahmoud noerat, 27, who died of a wound in the neck and ghassan qassem noerat, 16, who was shot in the chest
two other protesters were admitted with gunshot wounds, said the nurse, jehad alawni
in other developments, an israeli bus carrying arab workers to their jobs in israel was set on fire in the west bank town of halhoul, israel radio said. the arsonists evacuated the bus before setting it ablaze, the radio said
the palestine press reported additional clashes in bet ummar, near the west bank city of hebron and said the army closed hebron itself to some traffic. no further details were available
