iran and iraq lobbed long-range missiles into each other's capitals sunday and iran said its forces punched deeper into northeast iraq, moving closer to a key hydroelectric plant and oilfield
shipping officials reported iranian gunboats on sunday attacked the 24,529-ton indian tanker jainarayan vyas in the southern persian gulf, wounding one crewman and setting it on fire
the iraqis fired a long-range al hussein missile into tehran, a city of 6 million, the official iraqi news agency reported
another missile was launched on tehran and two into the central city of isfahan, ancient capital of the persian empire, said ina, monitored in nicosia
the iranians said the missiles hit residential neighborhoods, causing unspecified civilian casualties
the official islamic republic news agency in tehran said revolutionary guards fired two missiles at baghdad, which has a population of 5 million
the agency, also monitored in nicosia, said the missiles were aimed at ``two military targets'' in retaliation for iraqi missiles that hit tehran saturday, killing at least seven civilians and hitting an orphanage
baghdad radio reported one iranian missile hit a residential district of the iraqi capital sunday, demolishing houses, shops and cars. it said there were ``many civilians killed or wounded, including women and children.''
the radio made no mention of a second iranian missile
hundreds of civilians on both sides have been killed in missile, air and artillery attacks since feb. 29
tehran radio reported iran also fired four missiles at ``industrial and military installations'' in the strategic southern iraqi port of basra, and two other border towns further north sunday
in northeastern iraq, irna said revolutionary guards killed or wounded 700 iraqi soldiers to seize the southern shore of lake darbandikhan, high in the kurdistan mountains
it said an iraqi infantry brigade and an artillery battalion were severely mauled in a three-pronged attack in the 12-day-old offensive
the agency said the iranians destroyed 20 tanks and armored vehicles and captured 15 in annihilating the iraqi armored column when the iraqis made an abortive counter-attack
the fighting flared as the iranians broke out of their bridgehead on the eastern shore of the 10-mile-long lake in the strategic region east of iraq's kirkuk oilfields
iraq had no immediate report on the reported fighting
kirkuk accounts for 1.5 million barrels of oil a day, more than half iraq's oil production and vital for its war effort
irna said the revolutionary guards stormed the shaakh shamshir heights overlooking a big hydroelectric dam on the lake's southernmost point
the facility provides most of the power for the region as well as the capital baghdad, 120 miles to the southeast
by iranian account, the revolutionary guards control more than 40 square miles of iraqi territory east and south of the lake
iraq said saturday that the iranians had pushed 10 miles into kurdistan
