richard gephardt's tough trade message was a winner in chick's rooster lounge here _ just as it was in iowa. but gephardt never found the momentum from his iowa caucus victory and ended up a loser after michigan's caucuses
gephardt finished a distant third to jesse jackson and michael dukakis here, a state that should have been receptive to his trade message. but the auto industry-dominated state handed the missouri congressman his 28th defeat in 31 events this year and doomed his bid for the 1988 democratic presidential nomination
he is expected to formally withdraw from the race. gephardt scheduled a news conference monday afternoon in washington to announce his plans
gephardt's clear and consistent message _ a tough trade policy designed to protect american jobs _ resonated with workers worried about foreign competition
i like his enthusiasm, his `buy america' ideas. ... we have to take care of ourselves first,'' said bar owner chick mahoney, looking over a restaurant full of workers cheering gephardt
well-known on capitol hill as a leader in the house, but little-known across the country, gephardt never could transform enthusiasm about his message into victories
gephardt worked iowa hard with the message and won a narrow victory on feb. 8. but it wasn't much of a boost
gephardt got very little momentum out of iowa,'' said democratic party professional elaine kamarck. his win over paul simon was narrow and pat robertson's surprise second-place finish on the gop side over george bush dominated the news
once robertson mucked up the republican race, the democrats lost their best chance to have a giant among the candidates,'' she said
dukakis won his backyard primary in new hampshire the next week, but then gephardt went into south dakota and won the primary there feb. 23 with his trade message
but that was it for gephardt, except for a homestate win in missouri on super tuesday
bob squier, a democratic media consultant, said gephardt didn't freshen his message for the southern primaries on super tuesday and apparently didn't have the money to get his message out
if the hyundai had become a pickup truck as it crossed the mason-dixon line, it might have worked,'' squier said, referring to gephardt's centerpiece trade ad that singled out the korean car
squier said gephardt's campaign was guilty of ``kamikaze attacks in the south'' _ running a lot of ads in parts of florida, for example, where dukakis was very strong
gephardt's message also triggered counterattacks that he seemed unable to answer adequately
everywhere i go, they say he's the protectionist candidate. that is a great way for the opposition to smear you and get rid of your issue,'' gephardt told reporters at lunch one day in new hampshire
he strongly denied his policies were protectionist, but it was a charge that he could never shake
gephardt also had strong competition from the other candidates for his message
jackson, for one, has a powerful message to those worried about their economic situation. but jackson is an eloquent speaker of genuine force, while gephardt's rhetoric has been honed in the rarified halls of the capitol
and jackson says over and over again his message is one of hope and the future, while gephardt's emphasis on trade protections seemed to emphasize what cannot be done, not the possibilities to come
in addition, the missouri congressman was not known well outside of washington. kamarck said that poses a problem in laying out a strong message that some may not like, since the voters do not know enough about the candidate to trust him, even if they may have doubts about his message
gephardt's populist, anti-establishment themes also met with skepticism from reporters and others who knew him to be the consummate washington insider
his message also never brought him the organizational support he needed
the united auto workers stayed officially neutral, a major blow to his chances
in iowa, the state affiliate backed gephardt and gave him troops he used to win. in michigan, the uaw was badly splintered
