officials said the danube swept away sections of earthen dikes 15 feet high
many rivers in west germany, including the rhine, mosel, donlau and neckar, are flooding from heavy rains and rapidly melting snow in the alps
a 61-year-old coblenz man perished sunday after going to his flooded cellar to check the fuse box, police reported. they said he received an electrical shock, fell into the water and drowned
